					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-616774#post-1689569</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-616774/empty-nights#post-1689569</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 19 Jan 2013 01:12:22 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Zyn</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1404533</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p><em>Far from streaks of scattered lights</em><br /> <em>the end to all of mankind's plights</em><br /> <em>few would share these desolate sights</em><br /> <em>for naught was left but empty nights.</em></p> <p>Hauntingly beautiful. The dialogue is my favorite part, and I have always been fond of 1440. It was interesting to see the Third Brother being portrayed as he was, and the ending was very well done.</p> <p>Upvote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
